GameFOX CHANGELOG

Development issues: (let me know if you can fix this)
- GameFOX Options sometimes breaks in Mac platform
- GameFOX is not fully functional in SeaMonkey

Version 0.5.5.9                                             2008-06-21
======================================================================
- Update GameFOX site settings for use with new GameFAQs settings
  page

Version 0.5.5.8                                             2008-06-21
======================================================================
- (chrome/content/css/wide-layout.css): Allow board user navigation to
  be properly aligned to the right
- Update GameFOX board settings for use with new GameFAQs settings
  page
- Remove custom signature separator option
- Add pre-signature field, option to add newline before signature
- Truncate signatures at 2 lines. No other restrictions.

Version 0.5.5.7                                             2008-06-17
======================================================================
- Made the quick post form pretty
- Decode HTML entities when handling signatures and quotes
- Update the double click action on the active messages list for the
  new layout

Version 0.5.5.6                                             2008-02-03
======================================================================
- Fixed user highlighting, since I apparently broke it last release.
  Whoops!

Version 0.5.5.5                                             2008-01-30
======================================================================
- Firefox 3: This extension now provides secure updates.
- Linux: There are no longer any permission errors when adding CSS
  to the profile
- CSS developers: Highlighted posts now have a class
  (gamefox-highlight-(one|two)) to apply styles to in the event that
  your CSS breaks the integrated highlighter.

Version 0.5.5.4                                        August 13, 2007
======================================================================
- Fixed quoting not working in /gfaqs9

Version 0.5.5.3                                         August 5, 2007
======================================================================
- Fixed GameFOX not working correctly inside frames
- Descriptive window titles (gamefox.elements.titlechange) applies to
  frame container as well, but only for pages within the
  boards.gamefaqs.com host
- Fixed quoting in non-horizontal layout not removing QuickWhois
  information properly
- Removed alert box that appears when user trying to quote without
  having the QuickPost form enabled
- Updated GFCode tag support in quoting to use GFCode's quote header
  tags
- Updated Quoting Options page to reflect the updated quoting
  mechanism
- Reverted message numbering default style in horizontal layout to
  the original: "message detail  #001"
+ Added preference to change the message numbering style
  (Options|Page|Elements)

Version 0.5.5.2                                          July 25, 2007
======================================================================
- Fixed memory leak problem when displaying QuickPost
- Fixed Delete Purged (Tags) to conform to the new site response
- Updated Ricapar's Classic Theme CSS and GameFOX Default for Standard
  View CSS to conform to the recent ad changes
+ Assigned shortcut key for GameFOX Sidebar (Ctrl+Shift+Alt+G)
- Changed Toggle GameFOX Sidebar context menu appearance

Version 0.5.5.1                                         April 20, 2007
======================================================================
- Fixed issues with detail.php
- msglistDblclick: ignore double-click on images
- GameFOX Default CSSes: QuickWhois (".gamefox-quickwhois") can now be
  read clearly in some themes like GFCSS by using !important flag on
  some of the style rules;
  (Affected styles: background-color, padding)
- Front end: '+' in extension display name (GameFOX TK+) to reflect
  the different (current) author, changed update location, and other
  minor changes

Version 0.5.5.0                                       January 24, 2007
======================================================================
+ Reworked signature separator detection (for signature removal)
+ GFCode support for quoting (Options|Quoting)
+ gfaqs10: now detects page type based on page's structure
- QuickPost box/link now only shows when you have the ability to post
  (i.e. only if there's a post link)
- Logging in through GameFOX Sidebar, if successful, will redirect you
  to the currently opened GameFAQs page
+ Initial SeaMonkey support, credit to BenoitRen from MozillaZine
  Forum for porting GameFOX to SeaMonkey
+ Active Message List and Tracked Topics links in GameFAQs Tags
  context menu, customizable (Options|Mouse)
+ Sidebar: added Tracked Topics link
+ Clickable topic links in Tracked Topics (Options|Page|Elements)
+ Middle-click support (for opening a new tab) in GameFAQs Tags
  context menu, Pages context menu, Tag List (including the board
  titles), Sidebar links, Sidebar login button, and About dialog links
- Fixed typo in the Options dialog (thanks to Blue_Mage86, no more
  asterick and obelicks for you)
- Fixed Apply Board Settings (Options|Page|Message Board) not working
- Fixed QuickWhois not displaying user level
- GameFOX Default CSSes: horizontal scrollbar in QuickWhois if content
  overflows
- Wide Default Layout CSS: message hiding support
- Reverted QuickPost width to a slimmer size regarding issues with
  small screens
- Various tweaks

Version 0.5.4.1.20061117(.1)                         November 18, 2006
======================================================================
- Fixed signature removal not working correctly

Version 0.5.4.1.20061117                             November 17, 2006
======================================================================
+ Tagged board can be opened from Tag List using "Open in ..."
  context menu
+ Tagged board can be deleted from Tag List using "Delete Tag"
  context menu
- Fixed Delete Purged (Tags)
- Fixed two things in Ricapar's Classic Theme CSS:
  1. Redisplay Board Information in board list
  2. Remove "From:" in message preview
- Unicode (GameFAQs-compatible) character support for signature
  separator (especially for Firefox 1.5 support)
- Apply Site Settings (Options|Theme) now behaves as expected, cookie
  for display style setting will be kept until the end of the next
  year regardless of login expiration setting
- Various tweaks

Version 0.5.4.1.20061027                              October 27, 2006
======================================================================
- Code adjustment for New Posting Engine (10/25/2006)
- Fixed user highlighting not dealing with spaces correctly
- Changed topic highlighting table cells color from transparent to the
  actual highlight color
+ Descriptive window titles (Options|Page|Elements) now also applies
  to Post Message and Message Detail pages
+ Search Topics result page now behaves the same as topic list page

Version 0.5.4.1.20061022                              October 22, 2006
======================================================================
- Fixed "Post Message" button position in preview.php
- Apply Site Settings (Options|Theme) tweak

Version 0.5.4.1.20061020                              October 20, 2006
======================================================================
+ Full gfaqs9 support (thanks to Therum)
+ Enable "Post Message" button (Options|Page|Elements) now also
  applies to Preview Message page (preview.php)
+ New QuickPost error message for timed out requests

Version 0.5.4.1.20061019                              October 19, 2006
======================================================================
+ Automatic topic pagination (Options|Page|Elements), customizable
+ Clickable topic links in Active Message List (Options|Page|Elements)
+ Double-click and right-click support in Active Message List
  (Options|Mouse)
+ Customizable context menu items (Options|Mouse)
- Changed topic highlighting table cells color to transparent, might
  clash with this CSS rule:
  .even > td[style]:last-child { <some style>; }
- Changed font color of board titles in Tag List from solid black to
  gray (#DDDDDD)
- Improved internal CSS-pack version detection
- GameFOX Default for Standard View CSS: incompatible style removal,
  #footer detection, QuickPost font change
- Updated Options dialog

Version 0.5.4.1.20061016                              October 16, 2006
======================================================================
- Fixed a major bug: non-existent function call (String.trim)

Version 0.5.4.1.20061014                              October 14, 2006
======================================================================
- Fixed message hiding/highlighting
- Slimmer message hiding in horizontal layout
- Fixed topic highlighting
- Fixed quoting
- Hides Quote context menu if not on a message area
- Changed message numbering in horizontal layout: replaces
  "message detail" with "#001"
- Reverted message numbering in vertical layout to the original:
  "message detail | #001"
+ Apply button (stateless) in Options dialog
+ Options dialog now remembers last selected tab
- Context menu is displayed/hid correctly in non http(s) locations
- Updated CSS selection list in Site Settings (Options|Theme)

Version 0.5.4.1.061012                                October 12, 2006
======================================================================
+ gfaqs9 links (Options|Page): converts links in Pages context menu,
  Tags, Sidebar, and About dialog to gfaqs9 links if enabled
- Fixed descriptive window titles
- Fixed tag naming
+ Sidebar: added Wii and Feedback links
- Sidebar: changed Tag List box width from auto to 100%
- Hides Pages context menu if not on a topic row
- Wider topic page links (topic pagination) by using hard space
- Changed message numbering: replaces "message detail" with
  "message #001"
- Resets CSS combo box selection (Options|Theme) every time the list
  is updated
+ Total item number in the CSS combo box (Options|Theme)
+ Reload CSS button (Options|Theme): useful for applying style changes
  without having to restart the browser
+ About button in Options dialog
- Updated About dialog, links are now opened in a new tab in the most
  recent window

